---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import PolicyArticle from "../components/layout/PolicyArticle.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
---

<MainLayout title="Add-on Support">
  <PolicyArticle title="Crystord Add-on Support" updatedAt="June 8, 2026">

    <section>
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>Welcome to the Crystord support page. Here you will find resources to help you get started
      with the Crystord Google Workspace Add-on and the Crystord web application at
      <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a>, along with answers to common
      questions, troubleshooting steps, and how to reach us.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <h3>What is Crystord Add-on?</h3>
      <p>Crystord Add-on is a Google Workspace Add-on that synchronises variables between Google Sheets™
      and Google Slides™. Use it to create dynamic slide templates where placeholders like
      <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code> are automatically replaced with values
      from your spreadsheet. The Crystord web application at
      <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a> provides account management and
      authentication for the Crystord platform.</p>

      <h3>Basic Setup</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Install the Crystord Add-on from the
        <a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Workspace Marketplace</a>.</li>
        <li>Open your Slides™ presentation and add your variables in any part of your slides as
        <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code>.</li>
        <li>Click the bottom-left expansion arrow and press the Crystord icon to open the sidebar.</li>
        <li>The sidebar displays four buttons:
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Create Database:</strong> Creates a new Sheets™ file named "database" that
            the Crystord Add-on is authorised to read, and opens it in a new tab. This file is
            automatically selected and initially empty. Add your variables by filling the table with
            the columns "Name" and "Value".</li>
            <li><strong>Select Database:</strong> Allows you to select a previously created Sheets™
            file (database).</li>
            <li><strong>Open Database:</strong> Opens the selected database in a new tab.</li>
            <li><strong>Synchronise:</strong> Updates your current Slides™ file with the latest
            values from the selected database.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>The first step is always to create a database — no other functions work without it.
        After making changes to the database, click "Synchronise" to reflect updates in your slides.
        Use clear and consistent naming conventions for variables to avoid conflicts during
        synchronisation.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Crystord Web Application</h2>
      <p>The Crystord web application at <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a>
      is the sign-in and account management portal for the Crystord platform.</p>

      <h3>Signing in</h3>
      <p>Navigate to <a href="https://app.crystord.com">app.crystord.com</a> and enter your
      registered email address and password. If you have forgotten your password, use the password
      reset link on the sign-in page.</p>

      <h3>Sign-in issues</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Invalid credentials:</strong> Double-check that you are using the email address
        you registered with and that Caps Lock is not active.</li>
        <li><strong>Password reset:</strong> Use the "Forgot password?" link on the sign-in page to
        receive a reset email.</li>
        <li><strong>Account access:</strong> If you cannot access your account after following the
        above steps, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I install the Add-on?</h3>
      <p>Install directly via the
      <a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Workspace Marketplace</a>
      or from within Google Slides™ by opening the side panel and searching for "Crystord".</p>

      <h3>The variables in Slides aren't updating.</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure you have created and selected a database using the "Create Database" or
        "Select Database" buttons in the sidebar.</li>
        <li>Double-check that the variable names in your slides match exactly with the names in
        the database — matching is case-sensitive and spaces matter.</li>
        <li>Click the "Synchronise" button in the sidebar to update slides with the latest values
        from the database.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Do I need to re-link the Sheet every time?</h3>
      <p>No. Once a database is created or selected, it remains linked to the current Slides file.
      You can synchronise values as often as needed without re-linking.</p>

      <h3>What format should I use for variables in Slides?</h3>
      <p>Use double curly brackets: <code>&#123;&#123;variable_name&#125;&#125;</code>
      (e.g., <code>&#123;&#123;item_name&#125;&#125;</code>).</p>

      <h3>What if I accidentally delete the database file?</h3>
      <p>If the database file is deleted, create a new one using the "Create Database" button in
      the sidebar and re-add your variables. The database file is a standard Sheets file — you can
      also attempt to recover it from the Google Drive trash.</p>

      <h3>What if I select the wrong database?</h3>
      <p>Use the "Select Database" button in the sidebar to choose the correct file. Ensure the
      correct database is selected before clicking "Synchronise".</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

      <h3>Add-on not appearing?</h3>
      <p>Refresh Google Slides™ and ensure you are signed in to the same Google account you used
      to install the Add-on.</p>

      <h3>Sidebar won't open or is unresponsive?</h3>
      <p>Try closing and reopening Google Slides™, or reinstall the Add-on from the
      <a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Workspace Marketplace</a>
      if the issue persists.</p>

      <h3>Unexpected errors or bugs?</h3>
      <p>Take a screenshot or copy the error message and contact us using the details below. Include
      your browser version and a description of what you were doing when the error occurred.</p>

      <h3>Is the Add-on up to date?</h3>
      <p>The Add-on is updated automatically via the Google Workspace Marketplace. If you experience
      unexpected behaviour after a Google Workspace update, uninstalling and reinstalling from the
      Marketplace will ensure you are running the latest version.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact &amp; Feedback</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Support:</strong>
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a> — we aim to
        respond within three business days.</li>
        <li><strong>Bug reports:</strong> Include the error message, your browser version, and a
        description of what you were doing when the issue occurred.</li>
        <li><strong>Feature suggestions:</strong> We welcome your ideas — email us at the address
        above.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href={siteConfig.addonMarketplaceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Crystord on
        Google Workspace Marketplace</a></li>
        <li><a href={siteConfig.youtubeUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Crystord on YouTube</a>
        — tutorials and feature walkthroughs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

